    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Yes, I think it's okay to close it. If someone wants to provide an example of starting the kernel with gevent, that's probably wiki/cookbook material. It should only be a few lines:\n\n``` python\nfrom gevent import monkey\nmonkey.patch_all()\n\nstart_ipython_as_usual(sys.argv)\n```\n"
